<p>32 Warwick Square<br/>S.W.<br/>24-x-17</p>
<p>Dear Judge.<br/>I have two of your letters to answer - and feel ashamed at my negligence in not replying to thank you for writing so regularly, and so interestingly &ndash; I am afraid you have had a bad time lately with these infernal strikes &ndash; but I hope they are now a thing of the past, and that the government have learnt</p>
<p>(2)<br/>the lesson of taking a firm stand &ndash; Nell Knox wrote me that the girls have to volunteer as cooks etc. on the interstate boats. A pretty state of affairs.</p>
<p>You must be glad he has got over it all entirely.</p>
